This article is a presidential proclamation from October 9, 2009, declaring October 12, 2009, as Columbus Day in the United States. The proclamation recognizes Christopher Columbus' historic voyage across the Atlantic Ocean and its significant impact on the course of history. It acknowledges the transformation of North America into modern communities and highlights the contributions of Italian Americans to the nation. The proclamation calls for the observance of Columbus Day with appropriate ceremonies and activities, and for the display of the United States flag on public buildings in honor of Christopher Columbus.